## Learning Engine Requirements

The adaptive system must make decisions using multiple signals, not just correctness.

### Inputs that matter

* whether the answer was correct
* how long the student took
* how many hints were used
* recent streak behavior
* current mastery estimate
* current confidence estimate
* problem difficulty

### Outputs the engine must control

* next problem selection
* difficulty adjustment
* mastery score update
* confidence score update
* session summary

### Adaptive behavior

The system should generally:

* increase difficulty after strong performance
* reduce difficulty after repeated struggle
* stabilize when performance is mixed
* occasionally include review problems
* occasionally include stretch problems

### Recommended problem mix

* 70% near current target level
* 20% review / reinforcement
* 10% stretch / challenge

This should feel smooth to the student, not abrupt.

